<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="kind-adj">kind <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /kaɪnd/    美 /kaɪnd/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>仁慈的；友爱的；好意的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>It was</strong> really very <strong>kind of you</strong> to give me a lift home.
你让我搭便车回家，真是太好了。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>To avoid conflicts, we should be <strong>kind to</strong> one another.
为了避免冲突，我们应该友好相待。</p><footer>2012 江苏书面表达改</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="be-so-kind-as-to-be-kind-enough-to">be so kind as to / be kind enough to</h3>
<p>1.<strong>请您费心：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Will you be so kind as to shut the door? 
请您关上门好吗？</p></div></div>